Inline images retrieved from some versions of Lotus Domino sometimes are returned with a binary encoding type despite the fact that they are base64 encoded.  This causes JIRA to just store the base64 encoded data in the attachment file, which of course does not make a valid image.

A possible workaround is described in the attached patch, which basically forces JIRA's mail handler to treat inline attachments as base64 encoded.

